In this article, Vice President Mike Pence meets with Rosa María Payá, the daughter of Oswaldo Payá, a Cuban human rights activist who died in 2012. Payá continues her father's work advocating for human rights and democracy in Cuba. Pence expresses admiration for Payá and reassures her that the US supports the Cuban people in their fight for freedom, the release of political prisoners, and free and fair elections. Payá emphasizes the need for a democratic transition in Cuba and condemns the interference of the Cuban regime in other countries, particularly Venezuela. She calls for support from democratic nations to end the dictatorship in Cuba and restore democratic stability in the region. Pence commends Payá's courage and leadership and assures her of the US's commitment to supporting her cause.